SIMPLE: guinea_pig
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Guinea pig
<hw>Guin"ea pig`</hw> <ety>[Prob. a mistake for <ets>Guiana
pig</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small Brazilian
rodent (<spn>Cavia porcellus</spn> or <spn>Cavia cobaya</spn>), about
seven inches in length and usually of a white color, with spots of
orange and black. Called also <altname>cavy</altname>. It is the
domesticated form of the wild cavy, often kept as a pet and used
commonly as an experimental animal in laboratory research.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence,</specif> <mark>[figuratively]</mark>:
<def>Any animal or person used in an experiment; -- also applied to
people who are unwillingly or unknowingly subjected by authorities to
policies or procedures which might cause bodily or mental
harm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A contemptuous sobriquet.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<au>Smollett</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Guinea-pig director</ent>⟦br⟧
